text: Today is a day to commemorate and a day to salute. We commemorate the magnificent Challenger 7, whom we lost last year at this time, and we salute you, the men and women of America's NASA team. America will never forget that terrible moment a year ago when our elation turned to horror and then to grief and pain. Seven of our final missions have reached for the boundaries of space, where Earth ends and the path to the stars begins. In the next decade, we will build and fly a new space shuttle. Well the answer to that question is a resounding yes.
